puts "╚═════════════════════════════════╝".center(74)

puts "\nThe computer will generate a 4 color code, and the player will have 12 
chances to guess the code. The computer will provide feedback for each guess, 
placing key pegs underneath corresponding colors. A white key peg signifies a
correct color choice but an incorrect placement, a black key peg signifies 
correct color and placement.

If there are duplicate colors in the guess, they cannot all be awarded a
key peg unless they correspond to the same number of duplicate colors in the
hidden code. 

Once feedback is provided, another guess is made; guesses and feedback continue
to alternate until either the codebreaker guesses correctly, or twelve incorrect 
guesses are made."